Sentencas: Effective electrode materials play a key role to enhance electrochemical performances of symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells (SSOECs).
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Herein, exsolution effect of perovskite oxide at high temperature and reducing atmosphere is introduced.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: As a proof, La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-delta(LSFN) perovskite decorated with in situ exsolved Ni-Fe alloy nanoparticles is reported as electrode materials of SSOECs.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: XRD, SEM, TEM, and XPS characterizations prove the formation of Ni-Fe alloy.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The as-prepared SSOECs deliver improved electrochemical performances for both steam electrolysis (50%H2O/50%H-2) and co-electrolysis (50%H2O/40%CO2/10%H-2), current densities of 0.64 and 0.67 A.cm(-)(2) are obtained at 1.3 V and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) and distribution of relaxation time (DRT) analysis show that the in situ formed Ni-Fe nano-particles can provide a new reaction path for water/hydrogen half-reaction, and electrochemical activity and kinetics of oxygen evolution reaction (OER) can be significantly enhanced by RP type perovskite oxide after reoxidation treatment.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the SSOECs successfully runs for 60 h at 1.2 V without obvious performance degradation.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite with in-situ exsolved Ni-Fe nanoparticles as high activity catalyst for symmetric solid oxide electrolysis cells
